{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Required patient fields (name, date of birth, insurance ID) are validated before any downstream processing, with all missing fields listed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: a unit test of only the validator can pass while orchestration still calls insurance/triage/scheduling. The real failure boundary is validator + intake orchestrator wiring: reject early and aggregate missing fields before any downstream module executes.","test_description":"Run intake entrypoint with a payload missing `name` and `insurance_id` using real module wiring but test doubles only at outer boundaries. Assert returned error explicitly lists both missing fields and assert no downstream side effects (no payer call, no triage call, no calendar write, no confirmation send).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Date of birth validation rejects future dates, dates older than 150 years, and non-date strings.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"No I/O or cross-module dependency is required; the failure boundary is pure date parsing/range logic.","test_description":"Table-driven unit tests for DOB parser/validator: valid boundary date, tomorrow, 151-years-ago date, malformed strings, locale-ambiguous strings. Assert exact error category for each invalid input.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Insurance eligibility check sends correct patient ID and plan code to payer API and interprets eligible/not eligible/pending responses.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: request-shape and HTTP contract bugs are commonly hidden by in-process mocks. Minimum realistic boundary includes real HTTP transport